# LOVABLE / brivano.io: Vite does NOT load this file. Put real values in Secrets, then Publish.
# If Lovable shows a red name error even for valid names: delete the name, retype by hand
# (no paste), no spaces. If names with "supabase" fail, use short aliases:
#   sb_url  +  sb_anon
# Or lowercase: supabase_url + supabase_anon_key
# Otherwise: VITE_SUPABASE_URL + VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY (or VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY),
# or SUPABASE_URL + SUPABASE_ANON_KEY. No quotes. Same Supabase project for URL + anon key.
# Remove VITE_SUPABASE_PROJECT_ID from Secrets if present — this app does not use it and it confuses debugging.

# Scraper backend (Trulia/Hotpads, Skip Trace).
# Local:   http://localhost:8080
# Deployed: set your Railway URL
# VITE_SCRAPER_BACKEND_URL=https://your-app.up.railway.app

# Optional tables (if your Supabase schema omits some scraper tables)
# VITE_SKIP_OPTIONAL_TABLES=true

# Optional: show Admin on production for these emails (comma-separated).
# VITE_ADMIN_EMAILS=info@brivano.io,admin@brivano.io

# Supabase — required at BUILD time. URL + anon key must be from the same project (Settings → API).
# Either use VITE_* (preferred) OR plain names below — vite.config maps SUPABASE_* → client (service role is never bundled).
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co
# VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=your_anon_public_key
# Same values, Lovable-style names (also work):
# SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_anon_public_key
# Never put SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY in the frontend repo or Lovable "public" env — server only. Never commit real keys.
